JOY TO THE WORLD ft. @jordansmithlive Available now 🎄

We are in constant awe at the magnitude of Jesus's infinite, JOYOUS impact on every soul in the world. This song—especially the new chorus and bridge section we wrote with the talented Jordan Smith—is an expression of our gratitude for Christ’s singular gift of infinite joy. The gift that reaches all of us. The gift that saves all of us. The gift that we celebrate each Christmas season.

Together with Jordan, we hope this song stands as a reminder that the Savior’s gift transcends physical boundaries and difficulties, and that the birth of Jesus can truly bring a needed spirit of joy to the entire world. We felt a deep sense of joy adding our own creative flair to this iconic melody, and pray that even one person can discover a newfound sense of joy in Jesus.

❤️ - THIS IS JESUS team

–Joy to the World by Isaac Watts & Lowell Mason

–New music & lyrics by @mckaycrockett, Tyler Castleton, & @jordansmithlive

–Produced by @itsmykyl

–Mixed by @theotheredboyer

–Mastered by @diseromusic

Thanks for being here. God's been whispering some WILD dreams to me for the next decade and I can't wait to watch it all unfold with all of you.

IT'S HERE! Filming this music video was the experience of a lifetime. 😍

Words can't even describe the beauty of the locations where we filmed. 🤯

We saw so many different landscapes in our two days of filming that it felt like we had traveled around the world. 🌍

All that gorgeous scenery was a perfect backdrop for this video, but even more significantly, it was a powerful witness of God's power and goodness. His Creation is such a marvelous gift. 🎁

And yet it pales in comparison to the Gift that He gave us in the form of His Only Begotten Son, Jesus Christ—our Savior whose birth and life and gift of grace we celebrate this Christmas season. 🙏

We hope this video helps you feel close to Christ this Christmas season. And we also hope it makes you want to dance around the Christmas tree a little bit! 🎄

#musicvideo #joytotheworld #thisisjesus #jordansmith #christmas #christmasmusic #newmusic #newmusicfriday #happyholidays #merrychristmas

MARY DID YOU KNOW — When I first thought about doing this live show, @jordansmithlive was at the top of my list. His performance on this rendition of “Mary Did You Know” is just... unmatched. I honestly believe if he hadn’t been available, we might have reconsidered the entire show. How do you even find someone else to do justice to that track the way he does? He’s one-of-a-kind.
When he stepped on that stage, he delivered one of the best performances I’ve heard in my life. Easily one of the standout moments of the night. 💪🏻🔥

Go watch the full clip of “Mary Did You Know” + grab your tickets to see Jordan perform at The Birth Of A King Live at the Opry on 12/4 in Nashville - all available at the link in my bio!

✨ THAT’S A WRAP! ✨

Words can’t express the gratitude we feel. The joy we experienced. The love we received. Our first-ever This Is Jesus Christmas Tour exceeded all of our expectations.

Every night of the tour, a handful of God’s children gathered for one purpose—to lift the name of Jesus and experience His love, His grace, His mercy, His power, and His glory together.

Everyone involved in this tour was a vessel of God’s love.

We’ll never forget how it felt to watch Tauren, Katy, & Jordan take the stage together to sing This Is Jesus, Joy In The Morning, and more. 

We’ll always remember the humility, goodness, and raw talent of our incredible band (@thewhitebelts and friends), our fabulous background vocalists, and our stellar crew.

And, of course, we’re forever grateful for all of YOU—the audiences who came seeking Jesus and added your faith and love to the whole experience.

Before the tour, Tauren said that “Collaboration is part of the DNA of the kingdom.” And we saw so many manifestations of kingdom-building collaboration on this tour. It was truly a privilege to be part of something so powerful and unique.

We’re already making plans for the next This Is Jesus tour. Come join us.

📷: @jbirdyl
